{"TopicId":35842,"ForumId":44,"TopicTitle":"What would be the easiest way to OBLITERATE THE ENTIRE PLANET?","CreatedByName":"Kerbface","CreatedById":58573,"CreatedDateTime":"2013-07-04T07:07:17Z","PageNum":9,"Articles":[{"CreatedByName":"ChrisSpace","CreatedById":140622,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-11T07:41:27Z","Content":"\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223265327\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002235842\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221515652912\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n36 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n1.Say, a 20 km thick (high? deep?) layer of slaughterbots would be crushing any bot beneath. So, probably that would be the same planet with the upper lythosphere consisting of bots.\u003Cbr\u003E\n2.The bots need a lot of energy to extract the metals from oxides. Sun is poor one for a thick bot layer.\u003Cbr\u003E\n3.The bots produce energy and need a cooling. No cooling on several kilometer depth. They would melt.\u003Cbr\u003E\n4.The bots would be made of metals, so they should throw out the pure oxygen. A pure oxygen atmosphere would burn and melt the upper layers of bots.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt\u0027s more of a genocide weapon than a planet dissolver. (this goes for most other options too)\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223265327\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002235842\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221515652912\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n50 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIf treat that 43 kJ/kg as a kynetic energy, delta-V ~= (43000 * 2)\u003Csup\u003E1/2\u003C/sup\u003E = 300 m/s.\u003Cbr\u003E\nNot enough to significantly change the Earth orbit.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nBut enough to significantly change the orbit of, say, Mars for example. Enough to collide it with Earth, possibly.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223265327\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002235842\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221515652912\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n51 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nTotal available fusion energy calculated above is \u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(55,55,55);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-weight:300;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003E2.6*10\u003Csup\u003E29\u003C/sup\u003E J.\u003Cbr\u003E\nIf the rock velocity is 15 km/s, it is like a 2.3*10\u003Csup\u003E21\u003C/sup\u003E kg rock, i.e.3% of the Moon. It is like a total asteroid belt mass, but as you can see above, doesn\u0027t eliminate the planet at all.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n15km/s? Even diverting something from the Kuiper Belt would take a tiny portion of that.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223265327\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002235842\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221515652912\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n55 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(55,55,55);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-weight:300;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003ETo produce \u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(55,55,55);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-weight:300;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003Eantimatter one should spend more energy than it holds.\u003Cbr\u003E\nSo, total available antimatter energy would be several times lower than the mentioned total fusion energy. Just more compact.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nMake a small dyson swarm around the sun and aquiring energy won\u0027t be a problem.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cblockquote class=\u0022ipsQuote\u0022 data-ipsquote=\u0022\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentapp=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentclass=\u0022forums_Topic\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentcommentid=\u00223265327\u0022 data-ipsquote-contentid=\u002235842\u0022 data-ipsquote-contenttype=\u0022forums\u0022 data-ipsquote-timestamp=\u00221515652912\u0022 data-ipsquote-userid=\u0022129408\u0022 data-ipsquote-username=\u0022kerbiloid\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_citation\u0022\u003E\n57 minutes ago, kerbiloid said:\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003Cdiv class=\u0022ipsQuote_contents\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u003Cspan style=\u0022font-size:14px;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022color:rgb(55,55,55);font-family:\u0027Helvetica Neue\u0027, Helvetica, Arial, sans-serif;font-style:normal;font-weight:300;letter-spacing:normal;text-indent:0px;text-transform:none;white-space:normal;word-spacing:0px;background-color:rgb(255,255,255);float:none;\u0022\u003EIf you can turn a Sun, you don\u0027t need a beam to turn the Earth. Just do it directly.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/span\u003E\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003C/div\u003E\n\u003C/blockquote\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nIt takes far less energy to build such a weapon than it would to destroy a planet with it.\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"Findthepin1","CreatedById":139989,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-11T17:20:22Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nDelete the mantle\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\n\u00A0\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\nEDIT: put the mantle in low earth orbit\n\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cspan class=\u0022ipsType_reset ipsType_medium ipsType_light\u0022 data-excludequote=\u0022\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cstrong\u003EEdited \u003Ctime datetime=\u00222018-01-11T17:20:54Z\u0022 title=\u002201/11/2018 05:20  PM\u0022 data-short=\u00226 yr\u0022\u003EJanuary 11, 2018\u003C/time\u003E by Findthepin1\u003C/strong\u003E\n\u003C/span\u003E\n"},{"CreatedByName":"justidutch","CreatedById":99185,"CreatedDateTime":"2018-01-11T19:01:39Z","Content":"\n\u003Cp\u003E\nI\u0027ll bet there\u0027s a number of people out there who believe that if we keep tinkering with particle accelerators, we\u0027ll do the job easily enough\n\u003C/p\u003E\n"}]}